<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q52_v2" title="Q52_v2" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>
      Considera el punto 
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>C</m:mi>
        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        <m:mo>,</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
      </m:math>
      correspondiente a un vértice de un cuadrilátero dibujado en un plano cartesiano. Al trasladarlo, se obtiene el punto 
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>C</m:mi>
        <m:mo>'</m:mo>
        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
        <m:mo>,</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
      </m:math>
      mediante una traslación.
    </p>
    <p>
      ¿Cuál de los siguientes vectores de traslación lleva el punto 
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>C</m:mi>
        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        <m:mo>,</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
      </m:math>
      al punto 
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>C</m:mi>
        <m:mo>'</m:mo>
        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
        <m:mo>,</m:mo>
        <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
      </m:math>
      ?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>5</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si se aplica el vector (5, 3) al punto C(1, -2), se obtiene (1 + 5, -2 + 3) = (6, 1). Ese resultado es distinto de C&apos;(-4, -5), por lo que este vector no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mn>-3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! El vector de traslación se obtiene restando coordenadas: (-4 - 1, -5 - (-2)) = (-5, -3). Además, al verificar: (1 + (-5), -2 + (-3)) = (-4, -5), que coincide exactamente con C&apos;.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>-3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si se aplica el vector (-3, -5) al punto C(1, -2), se obtiene (1 + (-3), -2 + (-5)) = (-2, -7). Ese punto no es C&apos;(-4, -5), así que esta opción no corresponde a la traslación pedida.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si se aplica el vector (-5, 3) al punto C(1, -2), se obtiene (1 + (-5), -2 + 3) = (-4, 1). Aunque la coordenada x coincide, la coordenada y queda en 1 y no en -5, por lo que no llega al punto C&apos;.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso: hallar el vector de traslación</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar el punto inicial y el punto final</strong></p>
            <p>El punto inicial es</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>y el punto final es</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mo>'</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
              .
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular cuánto cambia la coordenada x</strong></p>
            <p>La componente horizontal del vector es la diferencia entre la coordenada x final y la coordenada x inicial:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular cuánto cambia la coordenada y</strong></p>
            <p>La componente vertical del vector es la diferencia entre la coordenada y final y la coordenada y inicial:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-3</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Escribir el vector de traslación</strong></p>
            <p>Entonces, el vector que lleva a</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
              hacia
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mo>'</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
              es
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-3</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
              .
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Verificar la respuesta</strong></p>
            <p>Si sumamos el vector al punto inicial, obtenemos:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-3</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                <m:mn>-5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>La verificación coincide exactamente con el punto final.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>